Interface Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback<L,NV>

  • Type Parameters:
    L - Type of the value resolved by the promise on which this callback is registered by calling Promise.spread(OnFulfilledSpreadCallback) or any of its overloaded variants. Must be a List.
    NV - Type of the value returned by the callback, which will be used to resolve the next promise in the chain.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback1<E,NV>, Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback2<E,E1,E2,NV>, Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback3<E,E1,E2,E3,NV>, Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback4<E,E1,E2,E3,E4,NV>, Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback5<E,E1,E2,E3,E4,E5,NV>
    Enclosing interface:
    Promise<V>

    public static interface Promise.OnFulfilledSpreadCallback<L,NV>
    Base interface for Promise.spread(OnFulfilledSpreadCallback), normally not used directly. Sub-interfaces are defined for 1-5 arguments; if more are needed, implement this interface with a Future<NV> onFulfilled method with the desired number of arguments matching the promised list.
